ation%20can%20also%20specify%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20the%20highest%20governance%20body%20has%20oversight%20of%20the%20design,%20implementation,%20and%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20tax%20governance%20and%20control%20framework.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-2-b%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOne%20example%20of%20a%20mechanism%20for%20individuals%20to%20raise%20concerns%20about%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20business%20conduct,%20or%20about%20activities%20that%20compromise%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20integrity%20in%20relation%20to%20tax,%20is%20whistleblowing.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EDisclosure%20207-2-b%20is%20related%20to%20Disclosure%202-26%20in&nbsp;GRI%202:%20General%20Disclosures%202021.%20If%20the%20information%20reported%20by%20the%20organization%20in%20Disclosure%202-26%20covers%20mechanisms%20used%20to%20raise%20concerns%20about%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20business%20conduct%20in%20relation%20to%20tax,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20reference%20to%20this%20information.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-2-c%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EDisclosure%20207-2-c%20is%20related%20to%20Disclosure%202-5%20in%20GRI%202:%20General%20Disclosures%202021.%20If%20the%20assurance%20process%20for%20disclosures%20on%20tax%20has%20been%20completed%20as%20part%20of%20another%20assurance%20process,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20reference%20to%20this%20information%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%202-5%20or%20elsewhere.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-3%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOrganizations&rsquo;%20tax%20practices%20are%20of%20interest%20to%20various%20stakeholders.%20The%20approach%20an%20organization%20takes%20to%20engaging%20with%20stakeholders%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20influence%20its%20reputation%20and%20position%20of%20trust.%20This%20includes&nbsp;how%20the%20organization%20engages%20with%20tax%20authorities%20in%20the%20development%20of%20tax%20systems,%20legislation,%20and%20administration.Stakeholder%20engagement%20can%20enable%20the%20organization%20to%20understand%20evolving%20expectations%20related%20to%20tax.%20It%20can%20give%20the%20organization%20insight%20into%20potential%20future%20regulatory%20changes%20and%20enable%20the%20organization%20to%20better%20manage%20its%20risks%20and%20impacts.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-3-a-i%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20approach%20to%20engagement%20with%20tax%20authorities%20can%20include%20participating%20in%20cooperative%20compliance%20agreements,%20seeking%20active%20real-time%20audit,%20seeking&nbsp;clearance%20for%20all%20significant%20transactions,%20engaging%20on%20tax%20risks,%20and%20seeking%20advance%20pricing%20agreements.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-3-a-ii%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20the%20approach%20to%20public%20policy%20advocacy%20on%20tax,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20can%20describe:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Its%20lobbying%20activities%20related%20to%20tax;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Its%20stance%20on%20significant%20issues%20related%20to%20tax%20that%20it%20addresses%20in%20its%20public%20policy%20advocacy,%20and%20any%20differences%20between%20its%20advocacy%20positions%20and%20its%20stated%20policies,%20goals,%20or%20other%20public%20positions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Whether%20it%20is%20a%20member%20of,%20or%20contributes%20to,%20any%20representative%20associations%20or%20committees%20that%20participate%20in%20public%20policy%20advocacy%20on%20tax,%20including:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E-%20The%20nature%20of%20this%20contribution;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E-%20Any%20differences%20between%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20stated%20policies,%20goals,%20or%20other%20public%20positions%20on%20significant%20issues%20related%20to%20tax,%20and%20the%20positions%20of%20the%20representative%20associations%20or%20committees.%20Disclosure%20207-3-a-ii%20is%20related%20to%20the%20requirements%20in%20GRI%20415:%20Public%20Policy%202016.%20If%20the%20organization%20has%20determined%20public%20policy%20to%20be%20a%20material%20topic%20and%20has%20reported%20information%20in%20GRI%20415%20that%20covers%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20public%20policy%20advocacy%20on%20tax,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20reference%20to%20this%20information.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-3-a-iii%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20the%20processes%20for%20collecting%20and%20considering%20the%20views%20and%20concerns%20of%20stakeholders,%20the%20organization%20can%20describe%20how%20the%20processes%20enable%20stakeholders%20to%20participate%20in%20this%20engagement.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20provide%20examples%20of%20how%20stakeholder%20feedback%20has%20influenced%20the%20approach%20to%20tax,%20the%20tax%20strategy,%20or%20the%20tax%20practices%20of%20the%20organization.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ECountry-by-country%20reporting%20is%20the%20reporting%20of%20financial,%20economic,%20and%20tax-related%20information%20for%20each%20jurisdiction%20in%20which%20the%20organization%20operates.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.1%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall%20report%20information%20for%20the%20time%20period%20covered%20by%20the%20most%20recent%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements%20or%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record.%20If%20information%20is%20not%20available%20for%20this%20time%20period,%20the%20organization%20may%20report%20information%20for%20the%20time%20period%20covered%20by%20the%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20immediately%20preceding%20the%20most%20recent%20ones.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.2%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-b,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.2.1%20reconcile%20the%20data%20reported%20for%20Disclosures%20207-4-b-iv,%20vi,%20vii,%20and%20viii%20with%20the%20data%20stated%20in%20its%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20for%20the%20time%20period%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-c.%20Where%20the%20data%20reported%20does%20not%20reconcile%20with%20the%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20the%20organization%20shall%20provide%20an%20explanation%20for%20this%20difference;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.2.2%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-ix,%20include%20corporate%20income%20tax%20accrued%20in%20the%20time%20period%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-c%20and%20exclude%20deferred%20corporate%20income%20tax%20and%20provisions%20for%20uncertain%20tax%20positions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.2.3%20in%20cases%20where%20an%20entity%20is%20deemed%20not%20to%20be%20resident%20in%20any%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20provide%20the%20information%20for%20this%20stateless%20entity%20separately.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-a%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20this%20Standard,%20tax%20jurisdictions%20are%20identified%20according%20to%20where%20the%20entities%20included%20in%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20in%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,&nbsp;are%20resident%20for%20tax%20purposes.%20These%20entities%20include%20permanent%20establishments%20and%20dormant%20entities.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EUnless%20otherwise%20stated,%20country-by-country%20information%20is%20to%20be%20reported%20at%20the%20level%20of%20tax%20jurisdictions%20and%20not%20at%20the%20level%20of%20individual%20entities.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ENumber%20of%20employees,%20revenues,%20profit/loss%20before%20tax,%20and%20tangible%20assets%20other%20than%20cash%20and%20cash%20equivalents%20are%20indicators%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20scale%20of%20activity%20within%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20considered%20in&nbsp;conjunction%20with%20the%20other%20required%20and%20recommended%20information,%20they%20can%20inform%20assessments%20about%20the%20level%20of%20taxes%20being%20paid%20in%20a%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%20information,%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20any%20other%20information%20relevant%20for%20understanding%20the%20scale%20of%20its%20activity%20within%20a%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20the%20reporting%20organization%20cannot%20report%20all%20required%20information%20for%20all%20the%20tax%20jurisdictions%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-a,%20it%20may%20use%20reasons%20for%20omission%20as%20set%20out%20in%20GRI%201:%20Foundation%202021.%20The%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20specify%20the%20requirement%20it%20cannot%20comply%20with,%20and%20to%20provide%20a%20reason%20for%20omission%20and%20required%20explanation,%20as%20set%20out%20in%20GRI%201.%20See%20Requirement%206%20in%20GRI%201%20for%20more%20information%20on%20reasons%20for%20omission.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20complete%20reporting%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction%20is%20not%20possible%20because%20the%20organization%20holds%20a%20minority%20shareholding%20or%20is%20the%20non-operating%20joint%20venture%20partner%20in%20an%20entity,%20the%20organization%20may%20provide%20&lsquo;information%20unavailable%20/%20incomplete&rsquo;%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20omission%20and%20specify%20the%20majority%20shareholder%20or%20operating%20partner.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20any%20contextual%20information%20necessary%20to%20understand%20how%20data%20has%20been%20compiled,%20such%20as%20any%20standards,%20methodologies,%20and%20assumptions%20used.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-i%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EDisclosure%20207-4-b-i%20requires%20the%20organization%20to%20report%20a%20list%20of%20entities%20by%20tax%20jurisdiction.%20If%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20publicly%20available%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20include%20a%20list%20of%20all%20its%20entities%20by%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20reference%20to%20this%20information.%20When%20reporting%20the%20names%20of%20the%20resident%20entities%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20specify%20if%20any%20of%20the%20entities%20are%20dormant.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-ii%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20its%20primary%20activities%20in%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20general%20description%20such%20that%20a%20report%20reader%20can%20clearly%20identify%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20main%20activities%20in%20the%20jurisdiction,%20for%20example,%20sales,%20marketing,%20manufacturing,%20or%20distribution.%20The%20organization%20is%20not%20required%20to%20list%20the%20activities%20of%20each%20entity%20in%20the%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-iii%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EEmployee&nbsp;numbers%20can%20be%20reported%20using%20an%20appropriate%20calculation,%20such%20as%20head%20count%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20time%20period%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-c%20or%20a%20full-time%20equivalent%20(FTE)%20calculation.%20To%20enable%20comparability,%20it%20is%20important%20that%20the%20organization%20applies%20the%20approach%20consistently%20across%20all%20tax%20jurisdictions%20and%20between%20time%20periods.%20If%20the%20organization%20is%20unable%20to%20report%20exact%20figures,%20it%20can%20report%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20to%20the%20nearest%20ten%20or,%20where%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20is%20greater%20than%201000,%20to%20the%20nearest%20100.%20The%20number%20of%20employees%20is%20one%20indicator%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20scale%20of%20activity%20in%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20number%20of%20employees,%20the%20organization%20may%20report%20the%20number%20of%20workers&nbsp;(excluding%20employees)%20performing%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20activities,%20if%20this%20helps%20explain%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20scale%20of%20activity%20in%20the%20jurisdiction.%20It%20is%20important%20that%20the%20organization%20reports%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20and/or%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20consistently%20across%20all%20jurisdictions%20and%20between%20time%20periods.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosures%20207-4-b-iv%20and%20207-4-b-v%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThese%20disclosures%20require%20the%20organization%20to%20report%20revenues%20from%20third-party%20sales%20for%20each%20tax%20jurisdiction%20and%20from%20intra-group%20transactions%20between%20that%20jurisdiction%20and%20other%20tax%20jurisdictions.%20Intra-group%20transactions%20within%20the%20same%20tax%20jurisdiction%20are&nbsp;not%20required,%20but%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20this%20information%20separately.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIntra-group%20transactions%20between%20jurisdictions%20can%20influence%20the%20tax%20bases%20of%20the%20organization%20in%20the%20jurisdictions%20involved%20in%20these%20transactions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIntra-group%20transactions%20within%20the%20same%20tax%20jurisdiction%20do%20not%20affect%20the%20tax%20base%20of%20the%20organization%20within%20that%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20this%20reason,%20revenues%20from%20third-party%20sales%20and%20intra-group%20transactions%20with%20other%20jurisdictions%20are%20a%20more%20appropriate%20indicator%20of%20an%20organization&rsquo;s%20scale%20of%20activity%20in%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction%20than%20aggregated%20revenues.%20Aggregated%20revenues%20could%20result%20in%20local%20revenues%20being%20double-counted,%20which%20might%20create%20a%20misleading%20impression%20about%20the%20organization's%20scale%20of%20activity%20in%20a%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20other%20sources%20of%20revenue,%20for%20example,%20dividends,%20interest,%20and%20royalties,%20where%20this%20is%20standard%20practice%20in%20the%20sector%20of%20the%20organization.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-vi%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20profit/loss%20before%20tax%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20calculate%20the%20consolidated%20profit/loss%20before%20tax%20for%20all%20its%20resident%20entities%20in%20the%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-vii%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20tangible%20assets%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20calculate%20the%20consolidated%20total%20of%20the%20net%20book%20values%20of%20tangible%20assets%20for%20all%20its%20resident%20entities%20in%20the%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-viii%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20corporate%20income%20tax%20paid%20on%20a%20cash%20basis%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20calculate%20the%20total%20actual%20corporate%20income%20tax%20paid%20during%20the%20time%20period%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-c%20by%20all%20its%20resident%20entities%20in%20the%20jurisdiction.%20This%20includes%20cash%20taxes%20paid%20by%20entities%20to%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20residence%20and%20to%20all%20other%20jurisdictions%20(e.g.,%20withholding%20taxes%20incurred%20in%20other%20tax%20jurisdictions).%20If%20the%20tax%20paid%20includes%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20withholding%20tax,%20the%20organization%20can%20explain%20this.%20If%20taxes%20are%20incurred%20in%20other%20tax%20jurisdictions,%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20amount%20of%20tax%20paid%20to&nbsp;the%20other%20tax%20jurisdictions%20separately%20and%20identify%20the%20jurisdictions%20where%20the%20tax%20was%20paid.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-b-x%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20difference%20between%20corporate%20income%20tax%20accrued%20on%20profit/loss%20and%20the%20tax%20due%20if%20the%20statutory%20tax%20rate%20is%20applied%20to%20profit/loss%20before%20tax,%20the%20organization%20can%20describe%20items%20that%20explain%20the%20difference,%20such%20as%20tax%20reliefs,%20allowances,%20incentives,%20or%20any%20special%20tax%20provisions%20where%20an%20entity%20benefits%20from%20preferential%20tax%20treatment.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20group%20explanatory%20items%20into%20a%20generic%20category,%20such%20as%20&lsquo;other&rsquo;,%20if%20these%20items%20together%20do%20not%20exceed%2010%25%20of%20the%20difference.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20the%20expiration%20date,%20investment%20requirements,%20and%20likely%20long-term%20continuity%20of%20tax%20reliefs%20or%20incentives%20for%20a%20jurisdiction.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20addition%20to%20providing%20a%20qualitative%20explanation%20as%20required%20by%20this%20disclosure,%20the%20organization%20can%20also%20report%20a%20quantitative%20corporate%20tax%20reconciliation.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20207-4-c%20and%20clause%202.1%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20report%20information%20on%20a%20regular%20schedule%20and%20make%20it%20available%20in%20time%20for%20information%20users%20to%20make%20decisions%20(see%20the%20Timeliness%20principle%20in%20GRI%201:%20Foundation%202021%20for%20more%20information).%20The%20organization%20is%20also%20recommended%20to%20report%20the%20information%20for%20the%20same%20reporting%20period%20and%20publish%20the%20information%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20its%20financial%20reporting,%20where%20this%20is%20possible%20(see%20section%205.1%20in%20GRI%201%20for%20more%20information).%20However,%20the%20information%20required%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4%20might%20not%20be%20available%20for%20reporting%20until%20a%20later%20point%20in%20time.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20the%20information%20required%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4%20is%20not%20available%20for%20the%20time%20period%20covered%20by%20the%20most%20recent%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements%20or%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20the%20organization%20may%20report%20information%20for%20the%20time%20period%20covered&nbsp;by%20the%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements,%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record,%20immediately%20preceding%20the%20most%20recent%20ones.%20Where%20this%20time%20period%20differs%20from%20the%20reporting%20period,&nbsp;the%20organization%20can%20specify%20the%20reason%20why.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.2.1%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20each%20of%20the%20disclosures%20specified%20in%20clause%202.2.1,%20the%20data%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20reconciled%20when%20the%20sum%20of%20this%20data%20for%20all%20tax%20jurisdictions%20equals%20the%20amount%20reported%20in%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements%20or%20in%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.2.3%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20providing%20information%20for%20stateless%20entities,%20the%20organization%20can%20also%20include%20their%20jurisdiction%20of%20incorporation.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.3.1%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETotal%20employee&nbsp;remuneration&nbsp;in%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction%20can%20reflect%20the%20business%20value%20provided%20by%20the%20entities%20in%20that%20jurisdiction%20to%20the%20organization%20as%20a%20whole.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETotal%20employee%20remuneration%20also%20represents%20the%20basis%20for%20calculating%20taxes%20withheld%20and%20paid%20on%20behalf%20of%20employees,%20covered%20under%20clause%202.3.2.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.3.2%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETaxes%20withheld%20and%20paid%20on%20behalf%20of%20employees%20refer%20to%20taxes%20withheld%20by%20the%20organization%20from%20employee%20remuneration%20to%20be%20paid%20to%20the%20tax%20authorities.%20These%20can%20include%20income%20taxes,%20payroll%20taxes,%20and%20social%20security%20contributions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Guidance%20for%20clause%202.3.3%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ETaxes%20collected%20from%20customers%20refer%20to%20taxes%20and%20duties%20charged%20on%20and%20collected%20on%20the%20sales%20of%20certain%20products%20and%20services.%20These%20are%20paid%20by%20the%20organization%20to%20the%20tax%20authorities%20on%20behalf%20of%20customers.%20Guidance%20for%20clause%202.3.4%20Examples%20of%20industry-related%20and%20other%20taxes%20or%20payments%20to%20governments%20include:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Industry%20taxes%20(e.g.,%20energy%20tax,%20airline%20tax);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Property%20taxes%20(e.g.,%20land%20tax);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Product%20taxes%20(e.g.,%20customs%20duties,%20alcohol%20and%20tobacco%20duties);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Taxes%20and%20duties%20levied%20on%20the%20supply,%20use,%20or%20consumption%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20considered%20to%20be%20harmful%20to%20the%20environment%20(e.g.,%20vehicle%20excise%20duties).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.3.5%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20significant%20uncertain%20tax%20positions%20for%20a%20tax%20jurisdiction,%20the%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20value%20of%20the%20tax%20positions%20in%20line%20with%20its%20audited%20consolidated%20financial%20statements%20or%20the%20financial%20information%20filed%20on%20public%20record.%20The%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20description%20of%20tax%20positions%20that%20have%20not%20been%20agreed%20with%20the%20relevant%20tax%20authorities%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20time%20period%20reported%20in%20Disclosure%20207-4-c.%20The%20description%20can%20include%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20disagreement%20and%20the%20reasons%20for%20any%20change%20in&nbsp;tax%20p